Hold the filter connector end up and flow isopropyl alcohol in through the
 fill hole, letting it drain out the gap between the pulser PCB and tube.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
This is the last chance to clean the filter by flushing fluid through the
 filter.
 Unless an optional drain hole is added to the output end of the filter
 it can only be cleaned by filling and draining through the same hole, which
 won't be as effective, once the cable connection is sealed.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Trim the pulse line cable and feed it through the pulse line hole in the
 end cap.
 If there is no connector on the cable yet this can be done after soldering.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The center conductor should extend from the dielectric by the width of the
 pulser PCB.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The shield should be trimmed back at least a couple millimeters from the
 dielectric.
 The entire filter will later be enclosed in a shield so a large gap here
 is okay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Enough shield should be exposed so it can be fed through the cap and still
 make significant contact with the tube.
 Even complete removal of the jacket is okay.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Solder the pulse line to the pulser PCB.
 Check to ensure a short between the pulser board and tube didn't develop.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Slide the end cap along the two cables until it is tight against the filter.
 Tape it into place, copper tape is recommended as it will provide some
 additional shielding but it just needs to keep the epoxy in place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Mix some epoxy and apply it generously through the fill hole in the end
 cap.
 It is recommended to degas the epoxy first to remove voids that could later
 cause discharges.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Hold the filter connector end up so the epoxy flows into the end cap and
 seals as it cures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Finishing touches
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If not done before, install the BNC connector on the pulse line and the
 HVconnector on the HV line.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the HV cable is unshielded then shield the cable with a foil shield.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
(Optional) Ensure a good electrical connection between the filter tube and
 exposed shield of the pulse line by connecting the two with low temperature
 solder or conductive epoxy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Using 3/4
