\end_inset

 shield braid apply braid to cover the filter end cap and at least an additional
 inch of the filter tube and HV cable.
 It should expand enough to go over the filter tube with the pulse line
 cable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the HV cable was unshielded extend the shield braid the length of the
 cable, it should narrow down enough to pull tight against the cable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Enclose the shield braid with heat shrink.
 A high shrink ratio heat shrink may be required to fit over the tube portion
 and shrink down enough to be snug around the HV cable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Double walled (adhesive lined) heat shrink is recommended, but use a strip
 of copper tape to ensure it doesn't interfere with good electrical connection
 between the filter tube and the exposed shield braid of the pulse line
 if a solid electrical connection wasn't ensured with low temperature solder
 or conductive epoxy.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
